26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_engine_sw_nv10.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:32 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "priv.h"
30#include "chan.h"
31#include "nvsw.h"
32
33#include <nvif/ioctl.h>
34
35/*******************************************************************************
36 * software context
37 ******************************************************************************/
38
39static const struct nvkm_sw_chan_func
40nv10_sw_chan = {
41};
42
43static int
44nv10_sw_chan_new(struct nvkm_sw *sw, struct nvkm_fifo_chan *fifo,
45 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
46{
47 struct nvkm_sw_chan *chan;
48
49 if (!(chan = kzalloc(sizeof(*chan), GFP_KERNEL)))
50 return -ENOMEM;
51 *pobject = &chan->object;
52
53 return nvkm_sw_chan_ctor(&nv10_sw_chan, sw, fifo, oclass, chan);
54}
55
56/*******************************************************************************
57 * software engine/subdev functions
58 ******************************************************************************/
59
60static const struct nvkm_sw_func
61nv10_sw = {
62 .chan_new = nv10_sw_chan_new,
63 .sclass = {
64 { nvkm_nvsw_new, { -1, -1, NVIF_IOCTL_NEW_V0_SW_NV10 } },
65 {}
66 }
67};
68
69int
70nv10_sw_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_sw **psw)
71{
72 return nvkm_sw_new_(&nv10_sw, device, index, psw);
73}
